2. The second algorithm is proposed in the paper titled "Intensity Prediction of Tropical Cyclones using Long Short-Term Memory Network" [2]. This paper introduces a stacked bidirectional long short-term memory network (BiLSTM) model for predicting the intensity of tropical cyclones, specifically in terms of MSWS. The model achieves high accuracy in predicting the MSWS up to 72 hours in advance. The BiLSTM network has been proven effective in capturing temporal dependencies and has shown promising results in various sequence prediction tasks.

